				<h1>Unemployment Rate and Unemployed Population for States from 2011 to 2015 </h1>
				<p></p>
				<p><b>Introduce</b></P>

				<p>Narrative Structure<br>

				The narrative structure is an interactive slide show.<br>
				The first slide is Map chart, the second slide is bar chart and the third slide is pie chart.<br>
				Click on the arrow on the top or bottom to next slideshow.
				</p>

				<p>Scenes<br>
				There are a total 3 scenes in this slideshow.<br>
				The 1 slide is map chart. It shows unemployment rate for each state. And, I use different colors to show different rate.<br>
				The 2 slide is bar chart. It shows unemployment rate by bar chart.<br>
				The 3 slide is pie chart. It shows total US unemployment rate.
				</p>


				<p>Annotations<br>
				Annotation 1: When you move to map, the color will change and show the state name and unemployment rate for each year.<br>
				Annotation 2: When you click vega editor of each bar chart, it will shows unemployment rate for states and show the state name. <br>  
				Annotation 3: When you move to pie chart, it shows how many people are unemployed and employed and show the rate. 
				</p>
				<p>Triggers<br>
				Triggers 1 : In 1 slide, we can click year to see different unemployment rate in different year.<br>
				Triggers 2 : In each slide, we can click arrow botton of top and bottom to go next slide or previous slide. <br>
				</p>

